<TITLE> Jalil to be paroled for overseas treatment, if necessary: adviser </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 2 (bdews24.com)Awami League general secretary Abdul Jalil will be paroled for treatment abroad, if necessary, home adviser MA Matin said Sunday. A new medical board was formed with five members for the AL leader, now hospitalised with heart failure and kidney ailments. "The board will submit a report by Sunday," Matin said in a news briefing at the home ministry. The announcement of probable overseas treatment for Jalilif recommended by the doctors of the new boardcame after a meeting at the Chief Adviser's Office where law adviser AF Hassan Ariff and Matin were also present. The medical board includes doctors from the Combined Military Hospital, Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University and medical colleges. A doctor treating Jalil at LabAid Cardiac Hospital said Saturday the health condition of the detained AL leader was unstable. "His condition is critical. He suffered mild heart failure on Friday night as his kidneys were not functioning," Dr Motiur Rahman, chief cardiologist of the hospital, told bdnews24.com. bdnews2
